            </messagepanel>
         </hazardstatement>
         <note>The isolator used for the external
backfeed protection must be rated according to the bypass on the rating
plate.</note>
         <p>Besides installing the external backfeed protection,
warning labels must also be placed:<ul>
               <li> on the system at the bypass input terminal <u>by the supplier</u>
               </li>
               <li> on the power isolator (the external backfeed protection) installed
upstream of the bypass input terminal <u>by the customer</u>
               </li>
            </ul>
         </p>
         <p>The warning label should contain the following text (or
equivalent in language(s) which are acceptable in the country in which
the system is installed):</p>
